<Action id="24152" issue="16972" author="kchristidis" type="comment" created="2017-05-22 17:40:10.0" updateauthor="kchristidis" updated="2017-05-22 17:40:10.0"> <body><! CDATA {quote}We recommend testing how long it takes to recover from a crashed broker (i.e how long until all partitions get new leaders), and setting the number of retries and delay between them such that the total amount of time spent retrying will be longer than the time it takes the Kafka cluster to recover from the crash - otherwise the producer will give up too soon. {quote} From the Definitive Guide book by the Kafka folks. This is partly what I'm trying to address by opening up this issue.  ></body> </Action>
